If you [**south**:: [[Learn in Public/Think/(1A1A3) Prefer to store useful ideas as idea elements\|(1A1A3) Prefer to store useful ideas as idea elements]]], then you need to ask yourself: "Is what I'm reading a..."

- Theory
- Model
- Definition
- Argument
- Counter-argument 
- Fact

If not, then discard it. Don't worry about adding it to your PKM. 

If it is, well, you'll need to decide if this particular element of information goes into your PKM. That's up to you. 

Although it may not be evident how a piece of information is useful at the outset, it's still important to decide what information should be retained. After all, [**Prev**:: [[Learn in Public/Think/(1A1) Writing Depends Upon Your Ability To Read\|(1A1) Writing Depends Upon Your Ability To Read]]]. If you try and retain everything, you'll retain nothing. If everything is important, nothing is. Etc.
